VOTE IDENTITY SYSTEM

🧩 Anyone can create a Vote Identity

A Vote Identity is a temporary governance object (proposal / decision / action).

NEW RULE:

ANY address can create a vote identity and attach it to ANY identity or cluster.

What this means

A vote identity can represent:

“John is President”

“Fire John”

“Join London cluster”

“Merge Ukraine + EU cluster”

“SOS emergency response”

Vote Identity structure:

Solidity

mapping(bytes32 => bytes32) public voteTarget; // identity or cluster

mapping(bytes32 => string) public voteMetadata;

mapping(bytes32 => uint256) public voteTimestamp;

Create vote identity

Solidity

function createVote(bytes32 voteId, bytes32 targetId, string memory metadata) external {

    voteTarget[voteId] = targetId;

    voteMetadata[voteId] = metadata;

    voteTimestamp[voteId] = block.timestamp;

}

